					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12710473#post-4401878</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12710473/scp-4437#post-4401878</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 19 Oct 2019 05:54:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>cybersqyd</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5336470</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Gonna say that yeah this is pretty fun, nice job :3</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;minor&nbsp;things</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;minor&nbsp;things</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <blockquote> <p>Current approximations are between 20&#160;km/s<sup>2</sup> to 57 years, and 20&#160;km/s<sup>2</sup> to 150 years.</p> </blockquote> <p>I feel like this should be cut down to &quot;Current approximations are 20km/s<sup>2</sup> to between 57 and 150 years.&quot;(EDIT: and probably merged into the previous sentence: &quot;The exact proportion is not known: current approximations&quot;)</p> <blockquote> <p>All temporal displacement of the train car ceases upon any personnel-created change in speed</p> </blockquote> <p>I'm a little iffy on the technicals of this: it seems like since you have to be accelerating to enter the anomaly, there'd be an expectation of that being a personnel-created change in speed since you had to do something to cause the acceleration/deceleration (but before you got into the temporal displacement)</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12710473#post-4401821</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12710473/scp-4437#post-4401821</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 19 Oct 2019 03:16:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Vincent Van Gone</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4874299</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Maybe it's because I've been struggling with writing dialogue myself, but I focused a little too much on it. I feel like the characters were well-developed, and I originally thought the dinosaur bit went on too long, it works well though.</p> <p>The idea itself was intriguing for me as well, and I feel like the ramifications are well presented. That's why I gave a +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
